---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Write code that is clear, readable, and maintainable for future readers.
- Prioritize clarity over cleverness; code should be easy to read, understand, and modify.
- Follow established coding standards and keep code well-structured to reduce errors.
- Refactor when appropriate to improve structure, readability, and maintainability.
- Leave the codebase cleaner than you found it.
- Stay within Detekt limits in `config/detekt/detekt.yaml` (notably `LongMethod` ≤ 60 lines). Prefer extracting helpers over `@Suppress`. After non-trivial Kotlin changes, run `./gradlew :libraries:<name>:detekt` or `./gradlew detekt` — lefthook/CI will fail otherwise.
